03/11/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- On Monday (1 November), Greece took over the rotating chairmanship of the Organisation of the Black Sea Economic Co-operation (BSEC) for a six-month period.
The handover from Georgia took place at a formal ceremony in Tbilisi late last week.
The BSEC unites 12 countries in the region.
(MPA - 02/11/04)
